                     <interp inst="t17831210-59-person720" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>Is there any other 
               <persName id="t17831210-59-person721">
                  Shaw
                   Ferguson
               <interp inst="t17831210-59-person721" type="surname" value="Ferguson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17831210-59-person721" type="given" value="Shaw"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17831210-59-person721" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             in the Roebuck book? - There is no other 
               <persName id="t17831210-59-person722">
                  Shaw
                   Ferguson
               <interp inst="t17831210-59-person722" type="surname" value="Ferguson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17831210-59-person722" type="given" value="Shaw"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17831210-59-person722" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             of any kind of spelling in the Roebuck book.</p>
               <p>Court. Have you examined the book thoroughly? - I have looked every name through with great care, and there is no name of 
               <persName id="t17831210-59-person723">
                  Shaw
                   Ferguson
               <interp inst="t17831210-59-person723" type="surname" value="Ferguson"></interp>
